
Open Burble 

URL =  http://www.haque.co.uk/openburble.php

=Description=

“essentially a framework, composed of 2m carbon-fibre modules, it had electronics embedded in 1000 helium balloons. Members of the public could configure and assemble these, inflate them and then unfurl the complex structure up to the scale of a 15 storey buidling. Finally, by shaking, rowing, twisting and bending a handlebar embedded with sensors (the same as in the Wii controller as it happens), dozens of people at once could have an effect on the Burble’s position and the colours streaming through it.”
(http://www.ugotrade.com/2009/01/28/pachube-patching-the-planet-interview-with-usman-haque/)

